70.7	Simplified_Chinese_characters	Simplified Chinese characters	Simplified Chinese characters (simplified Chinese: ; traditional Chinese: ; Pinyin: Jiǎntǐzhōngwén) are standardized Chinese characters prescribed in the Xiandai Hanyu Tongyong Zibiao (List of Commonly Used Characters in Modern Chinese) for use in mainland China. Along with traditional Chinese characters, it is one of the two standard character sets of the contemporary Chinese written language. The government of the People's Republic of China in mainland China has promoted them for use in printing since the 1950s and 1960s in an attempt to increase literacy. They are officially used in the People's Republic of China and Singapore.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a4/Chinese_characters_logo.jpg
